metadata.name: The Bitbrain Open Access Sleep (BOAS) dataset
metadata.dataset_summary: This dataset bridges clinical sleep monitoring and wearable EEG technologies, containing data from 128 nights where participants were simultaneously monitored with a Brain Quick Plus Evolution PSG system and a Bitbrain wearable EEG headband. The dual-recording approach allows for direct comparison and validation of the wearable EEG device against the established PSG standard, providing a rich resource for evaluating wearable EEG technology in sleep studies.
metadata.task_description: Participants underwent simultaneous monitoring with a Brain Quick Plus Evolution PSG system and a wearable EEG headband for 128 nights. Three expert sleep scorers independently annotated the PSG recordings following AASM criteria, and a consensus label was derived. This consensus was used to train a deep learning model for automatic sleep scoring, validated separately on PSG and wearable EEG data. The task involved natural sleep, with data collected to compare and validate wearable EEG against clinical PSG for sleep staging.
